description.narrative: In 2021, in Haiti, UNICEF enabled solar-powered;cold chain coverage to reach 96% of health institutions, which greatly facilitated the storage and availability of vaccines at peripheral level, while guaranteeing quality. The implementation of the RED approach has been strengthened in the departments, which has made it possible to maintain vaccination coverage for tracer antigens around the same performance from previous years despite socio-security crisis and fuel shortage.Over 60 health facilities were equipped with medical products and equipment (including 20 EmONC) by UNICEF for better maternal, neonatal and child health services, in addition to capacity building of health providers.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/01/2022
